Question 3
Which of the following is/are true about odds ratio (OR) and relative risk (RR)? (SELECT ALL THAT APPLY)

1 / 1 point

The OR has better statistical properties, but, in general, is less intuitive to interpret than the RR.

Correct

The OR is more conservative than the RR, especially when the event is common.


Both the OR and the RR are valid measures of association/treatment effect.

Correct

The OR is a good estimate of the RR when the event is rare in both treatment and comparison groups.

Correct

Question 4
Which of the following is/are true about meta-analysis? (SELECT ALL THAT APPLY)

1 / 1 point

A high quality meta-analysis gets rid of heterogeneity that might be observed across individual studies.


Meta-analysis provides a single estimate of an effect size (with an associated confidence interval) with information from all relevant individual studies.

Correct

The meta-analytic effect size usually has greater precision than individual study effect sizes.

Correct

Meta-analysis allows the statistical evaluation of homogeneity/heterogeneity of results.

Correct
